**Explanation:**

1. **Standard Notes** stands out with its powerful end-to-end encryption, audited security, and unparalleled privacy features, making it the top recommendation[1][2].

2. **Joplin** is open-source with strong privacy focus and E2EE, supporting multimedia notes and extensive customization[3].

3. **AnyType** offers local, on-device end-to-end encryption with maximum data privacy and an innovative object-based note-taking system[4].

4. **Apple Notes** provides secure iCloud syncing with privacy for Apple ecosystem users[2].

5. Other well-known note apps like **Simplenote, Notion, Evernote, Microsoft OneNote, Obsidian, Bear, Zoho Notebook, Turtl, Boostnote, Nimbus Note, Dropbox Paper, Google Keep, Craft, Agenda, Roam Research, GoodNotes** are broadly popular and have varying degrees of security and privacy features; many support encryption or sync security, although not all are primarily focused on privacy.

The above list is ordered primarily on **security and privacy**, with apps like Standard Notes, Joplin, and AnyType leading due to their end-to-end encryption and open-source transparency. The remainder are included for completeness and general high ranking in note-taking capabilities with reasonable privacy standards.